  "instructions": [
    "In a large pot, combine the tonkotsu broth, sesame oil, ginger, garlic, miso paste, soy sauce, and rice vinegar. Bring to a simmer over medium heat.",
    "Add the kombu seaweed to the pot and cook for 10 minutes, or until the flavors have melded together.",
    "Meanwhile, cook the noodles according to the package instructions. Drain and set aside.",
    "In a large bowl, combine the cooked noodles, sliced scallions, pickled ginger, and grated sesame seeds.",
    "Strain the broth through a fine-mesh sieve into a clean pot, discarding the solids.",
    "Add the cooked noodles to the pot and top with a slice of pickled ginger, a few strands of scallions, and a sprinkle of grated sesame seeds.",
    "Serve immediately and garnish with additional scallions and sesame seeds, if desired."
  ],
